The government will scrap the religious exemption from welfare benefits . 
 Scott Morrison has announced parents will be cut from childcare benefits if they don't immunise their children . 
 The welfare ban comes into force from January 1, 2016 . 
 Parents who refuse to immunised their kids are set to lose up to $15,000 . 
 These include Family Tax Benefit A as well as childcare assistance . 
 Scott Morrison said rules around welfare payments need to be 'tightened'